			<ns0:name>nfulla...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/118309011164612460950/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">One reason for 3d testing not enabled is many of the bots do not have 3D HW, or the bot itself is run within a virtual machine.

To fully enable 3D testing on the bots, we need a white-listed 3D HW &amp; driver on the bots (including try bots)

Another alternative is to test against a software rendered Mesa back end in chrome, but this is far from optimal, and does not represent "real world" use of 3D.

We should also have a MacBook Pro w/ dual GPU as part of the test plan.

I'm looking into re-enabling what can be re-enabled for now.
